          <element elementId="41">
            <name>Description</name>
            <description>An account of the resource</description>
            <elementTextContainer>
              <elementText elementTextId="329">
                <text>RECORD ONE, SIDE ONE:    &#13;
Dinah Washington, "The Blues Ain't Nothing But a Woman Cryin For Her Man"; Cannonball Adderly with Machito and his Orchestra, "Cannonology"; Harry Belafante with Machito and his Orchestra, "Lean on Me"; Herbie Mann with Machito and his Orchestra, "Carabunta"; Steve Allen's Roundtable All-Stars, "I Thought About You"; Chris Connor and Maynard Ferguson, "I Feel a Song Coming On".&#13;
&#13;
RECORD ONE, SIDE TWO:&#13;
Louis Armstrong and Duke Ellington, "Cotton Tail"; John Coltrane Quartet, "Exotica"; Dizzy Gillespie, "Paris Swing"; Erroll Garner, "Love for Sale"; Woody Herman Sextet with Nat Adderley, "Lullaby of Birdland"; Charlie Parker &amp; Miles Davis, "Klactoveededstene"&#13;
&#13;
RECORD TWO, SIDE ONE:&#13;
Stan Getz &amp; Horace Silver, "Strike Up the Band"; Art Tatum, "Dark Eyes"; Dizzy Gillespie &amp; Charlie Parker, " Groovin' High"; J. J. Johnson &amp; Kai Winding, "The Shrike"; Bud Powell, "Off Minor"; Joe Newman &amp; Zoot Sims, "Tater Pie"&#13;
&#13;
RECORD TWO, SIDE TWO:&#13;
Joe Williams With Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, "Everyday"; Sarah Vaughan with Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, "Until I Met You"; Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, "Tickle Toe"; Joe Williams with Lambert, Hendricks &amp; Ross with Count Basie &amp; His Orchestra, "Going to Chicago Blues"; Billy Eckstine with Count Basie &amp; his Orchestra, "Jelly, Jelly"; Tony Bennett with count Basie &amp; his Orchestra, "I Guess I'll Have to Change My Plans"&#13;
</text>
              </elementText>
            </elementTextContainer>
